1 (a) 1. A health benefit plan[ issued or renewed on or after January 1, 2022,]
2 that provides coverage for treatment of a mental health condition shall
3 provide coverage of any treatment of a mental health condition under
4 terms or conditions that are no more restrictive than the terms or
5 conditions provided for treatment of a physical health condition.
6 2. Expenses for mental health and physical health conditions shall be
7 combined for purposes of meeting deductible and out-of-pocket limits
8 required under a health benefit plan.
9 3. A health benefit plan that does not otherwise provide for management of
10 care under the plan or that does not provide for the same degree of
11 management of care for all physical health or mental health conditions
12 may provide coverage for treatment of mental health conditions through
13 a managed care organization;
14 (b) With respect to mental health condition benefits in any classification of
15 benefits, a health benefit plan required to comply with paragraph (a) of this
16 subsection shall not impose:
17 1. A nonquantitative treatment limitation that does not apply to medical
18 and surgical benefits in the same classification; and
19 2. Medical necessity criteria or a nonquantitative treatment limitation
20 unless, under the terms of the plan, as written and in operation, any
21 processes, strategies, evidentiary standards, or other factors used in
22 applying the criteria or limitation to mental health condition benefits in
23 the classification are comparable to, and are applied no more stringently
24 than, the processes, strategies, evidentiary standards, or other factors
25 used in applying the criteria or limitation to medical and surgical
26 benefits in the same classification; and
27 (c) Paragraph (b) of this subsection shall be construed to require, at a minimum,
